R was created by two professors, **Ross Ihaka** and **Robert Gentleman**, from the University of Auckland in the early 1990s. @cr-img

Inspired by S programming language, this pioneering duo developed a language to teach introductory statistics at the University of Auckland and named it after the **initial** of their first names. [@cr-img]{highlight="cr-initial,cr-initial1"}

Their vision of a free and open-source platform for statistical computing has since empowered countless data enthusiasts and professionals worldwide, creating a vibrant community that continues to innovate and expand the boundaries of R. @cr-img

:::{#cr-img}

::: {.columns}

::: {.column width="50%}
